<section id='starter-guide'>
	<p>The color schemas below are suggestions for graphics. Feel free to be more creative when designing stand-along projects. </p>
    <p class='x-large'><strong>Font</strong></p>
    <p>We usually use <b>"benton-sans-regular"</b> for the main article to keep our style in consistent with NJ.com articles. But you can get creative when styling the headline. </p>
    <p>Here are some other fonts our coworkers at New Jersey Best like. </p>
    <p class='x-large'><strong>HEADLINES: Playfair Black (Google font)</strong></p>
    <p class="Playfair_bold xxx-large">
        abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz<br/>ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ<br/>12345678910</p>
    <p class='x-large'><strong>Body Sub Header: Lato Black (Google font)</strong></p>
    <p class="Lato_black large">abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz<br/>ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ<br/>123456789</p>
    <p class='x-large'><strong>Use sparingly: Caveat (Google font)</strong></p>
    <p class="Caveat xxx-large">abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz<br/>ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ<br/>123456789</p>
    <p class='x-large'><strong>Font size</strong></p>
    <p>For the main article, we use "medium" for large screen: <br/> "font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.65; margin: 1.5rem 0;". </p>
    <p>We use "root" for mobile: <br/> "font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.65; margin: 1.5rem 0;" </p>
    <p>Check out <strong>variables.styl</strong> for these definitions below. Check out <strong>guide.hbs</strong> to see how to use them.</p>
